1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,250
A few months ago, a former student of mine, in business for just four years, opened her fourth hardware store.

2
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:15,490
This was quite a feat, considering the young lady's small initial capital investment of only $3,500,

3
00:00:15,680 --> 00:00:21,250
strong competition from other stores, and the relatively short time she had been in business.

4
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:28,210
I visited her new store shortly after it opened, to congratulate her on the fine progress she had made.

5
00:00:28,639 --> 00:00:35,970
In an indirect way, I asked her how she was able to make a success of three stores and open a fourth one,

6
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:40,530
when most merchants had to struggle to make a success of just one store.

7
00:00:41,119 --> 00:00:49,250
Naturally, she answered, I worked hard, but just getting up early and working late isn't responsible for the four stores.

8
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:51,970
Most people in my business work hard.

9
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:58,210
The main thing I attribute my success to is my self-styled weekly improvement program.

10
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,609
A weekly improvement program?

11
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:01,970
Sounds impressive.

12
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,169
How does it work?

13
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,050
I asked.

14
00:01:04,639 --> 00:01:08,129
Well, it really isn't anything elaborate, she continued.

15
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:13,090
It's just a plan to help me do a better job as each week rolls around.

16
00:01:13,359 --> 00:01:18,850
To keep my forward thinking on the track, I've divided my job into four elements,

17
00:01:19,119 --> 00:01:23,010
customers, employees, merchandise, and promotion.

18
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:29,409
All during the week I make notes and jot down ideas as to how I can improve my business.

19
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:39,970
Then, every Monday evening, I set aside four hours to review the ideas I've jotted down and figure out how to put the solid ones to use in the business.

20
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:45,810
In this four-hour period, I force myself to take a hard look at my operation.

21
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:49,810
I don't simply wish more customers would shop in my store.

22
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:54,689
Instead, I ask myself, what can I do to attract more customers?

23
00:01:54,879 --> 00:01:58,210
How can I develop regular, loyal customers?

24
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:05,169
She went on describing numerous little innovations that made her first three stores so successful.

25
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:17,730
Things like the way she arranged the merchandise within her stores, her suggestion selling technique that sold two out of three customers merchandise they had not planned to buy when they entered her stores.

26
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:23,250
The credit plan she devised when many of her customers were out of work because of a strike.

27
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:28,050
The contest she developed that boosted sales during a slack season.

28
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:33,250
I ask myself, what can I do to improve my merchandise offerings?

29
00:02:33,359 --> 00:02:34,770
And I get ideas.

30
00:02:35,119 --> 00:02:37,090
Let me cite just one case.

31
00:02:37,359 --> 00:02:43,169
Four weeks ago, it occurred to me that I should do something to get more youngsters into the store.

32
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:47,490
I reasoned if I had something here to draw the kids to the store,

33
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,810
I'd also draw more of the parents.

34
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:53,409
I kept thinking about it, and then this idea came.

35
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:59,250
Put in a line of small carted toys for children in the four to eight age bracket.

36
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,450
It's working.

37
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:04,129
The toys take little space, and I make a nice profit on them.

38
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:08,369
But most important, the toys have increased store traffic.

39
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:13,090
Believe me, she went on, my weekly improvement plan works.

40
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:19,649
Just by conscientiously asking myself, how can I do a better job, I find the answers.

41
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:27,250
It's a rare Monday night that I don't come up with some plan or technique that makes that profit and loss statement look better.

42
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:35,730
And I've learned something else, too, about successful merchandising, something that I think every person going into business for himself should know.

43
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,409
What's that, I asked?

44
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:42,609
Just this, it isn't so much what you know when you start that matters,

45
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:48,290
it's what you learn and put to use after you open your doors that counts most.

